## 1. Introduction

A mobile application will be created to allow members of the GIU community to report issues related to infrastructure, maintenance, sustainability, and cleanliness that need the attention of the Facility Management team. Examples of such issues include broken doors, flickering lights, open windows while the air conditioning is running, and overflowing trash bins.

The system will enable the Facility Management team to receive these reports, assign the appropriate personnel, and monitor and update the status of each issue. Status updates will be visible to the users who submitted the reports.

This application aims to support efficient campus maintenance and help preserve campus assets. It is expected to improve response times to reported problems, resulting in a cleaner, safer, and more comfortable environment for community members.

The solution will be developed as a mobile application using **React Native with Expo**, supported by a backend built with **Node.js and RESTful APIs**.

This Software Requirements Specification (SRS) document provides a comprehensive overview of the GIU Facility Management Mobile Application. It is intended for developers, project managers, testers, and stakeholders to ensure a common understanding of the proposed system.

---

### 1.1 Product Vision & Scope

The vision of the GIU Facility Management Mobile Application is to create a seamless, efficient, and collaborative platform that empowers every member of the GIU community to participate in maintaining campus facilities, while enabling the Facility Management team to deliver faster, more effective service.

**The scope includes:**
- A mobile application for Android and iOS built with React Native and Expo
- User authentication with four roles: Community Member, Facility Manager, Worker, and Admin
- Ticket submission with photo attachment, location selection, category choice, and description
- Real-time notifications for submission confirmation and status changes
- Dashboard for managers to view, filter, and assign tickets
- Worker view showing assigned tasks with ability to update progress and status
- Admin functions for user management and system configuration
- Secure cloud storage for images
- PostgreSQL database backend with RESTful APIs

