## 3. Functional Requirements

### 3.1 Community Member Functional Requirements

| ID | Name | Description |
|----|------|-------------|
| FR-CM-01 | Register | The system shall allow a Community Member to register by providing required information (name, email, password). |
| FR-CM-02 | Login | The system shall allow a Community Member to log in using a valid email and password. |
| FR-CM-03 | Issue Submission | The system shall allow a Community Member to submit an issue including: Location, Photo, Category, Description. |
| FR-CM-04 | Add Description & Category | The system shall allow users to choose a ticket category (electrical, plumbing, cleanliness, sustainability) and enter a short textual description. |
| FR-CM-05 | View Submitted Issues | The system shall allow users to view a list of all their submitted issues. |
| FR-CM-06 | View Issue Status | The system shall display the current status of an issue (Pending / In Progress / Resolved) to the Community Member. |
| FR-CM-07 | Logout | The system shall allow a Community Member to log out of the application. |
| FR-CM-08 | View Ticket Details *(extra)* | The system shall allow users to open a ticket and view its full details (photos, description, category, location, status history, timestamps). |
| FR-CM-09 | Search/Filter Tickets *(extra)* | The system shall allow users to search and filter tickets by category, status, and location. |

