## 4. Non-Functional Requirements

### 4.1 Performance Requirements

| ID | Name | Requirement |
|----|------|-------------|
| NFR-01 | Response Time | The system shall load any mobile application screen within 5 seconds under normal internet conditions. |
| NFR-02 | Ticket Submission Time | The system shall complete ticket submission, including image upload, within 10 seconds on a stable internet connection. |

---

### 4.2 Availability and Reliability Requirements

| ID | Name | Requirement |
|----|------|-------------|
| NFR-03 | System Availability | The system shall be operational during official university working hours. |
| NFR-04 | Data Persistence | All submitted tickets and status updates shall be permanently stored in the PostgreSQL database to prevent data loss. |

---

### 4.3 Security Requirements

| ID | Name | Requirement |
|----|------|-------------|
| NFR-05 | Authentication | Users shall be required to log in before accessing any system functionality. |
| NFR-06 | Authorization (RBAC) | The system shall enforce role-based access control to restrict actions according to user roles (Community Member, Worker, Manager, Admin). |
| NFR-07 | Secure Communication | All communication between the mobile application and backend server shall be secured using HTTPS. |
| NFR-08 | Password Protection | User passwords shall be stored using secure hashing algorithms (e.g., bcrypt). |

---

### 4.4 Usability Requirements

| ID | Name | Requirement |
|----|------|-------------|
| NFR-09 | Ease of Ticket Submission | A community member shall be able to submit a ticket in less than one minute. |
| NFR-10 | User Interface Clarity | The system shall provide a simple, clear, and intuitive user interface suitable for non-technical users. |

---

### 4.5 Compatibility Requirements

| ID | Name | Requirement |
|----|------|-------------|
| NFR-11 | Mobile Compatibility | The application shall operate on Android and iOS devices using React Native with Expo. |
| NFR-12 | Database Technology | The system shall utilize PostgreSQL as the relational database management system. |

---

### 4.6 Maintainability Requirements

| ID | Name | Requirement |
|----|------|-------------|
| NFR-13 | Modular Architecture | The backend system shall follow a modular and layered architecture (routes, controllers, services) to facilitate future maintenance and updates. |

